pageContext.claim: “We got everything [from North Korea]. There's no missiles, we got our hostages back, we have the remains coming back -- everything.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump highlights the visible fruits of his talks with North Korea. But The Washington Post reported in June that U.S. intelligence officials, citing newly obtained evidence, have concluded that North Korea does not intend to fully surrender its nuclear stockpile, and instead is considering ways to conceal the number of weapons it has and secret production facilities.
